The paper focuses on physical-layer security in a small cell network with cooperative cache-enabled small base stations, which involves information theory (IT) and network infrastructure (NI). The presence of eavesdroppers also suggests a focus on cryptography (CR). The caching placement strategy and transmission techniques involve multimedia (MM) and signal processing (SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.MM, and cs.SI.
